{"name": "Put It On ft. Cyanca 1/24", "description": ""Put It On" is a song about repping and cheering on your authentic self and values as one would rep and cheer their hometown, favorite sports team, artist or anything they feel passionate about.

For quite some time, I lacked confidence and lost sight of my identity at a young age. From my early teenage years I grew up in a toxic church culture that never celebrated my gifting in music. As a matter of fact, it was discouragedb�&publicly, in front of an audience of 3,000+ people. That and other traumatic experiences while at this church would damage my view of self and made me believe I wasnb�t good enough.

However, through wise counsel and therapy over the past year, love from friends & family, prayer and time to reflect, Ib�ve finally arrived at the point of a confidence like no other. I no longer wonder if Ib�m good or good enoughb�&I AM great and I am continuously pursuing greatness.

While living in this new confidence, this song came in the form of beat produced by yours truly. The hook? Me chanting & cheering myself on and manipulating my vocal takes to sound like a crowd of sampled people chanting. I got together with a good friend of mine and incredible artist, Cyanca and the words just poured out of both of us and was recorded in two short studio sessions.

I want this song to encourage and uplift anyone who has dealt with traumatic experiences to be confident in who they are and the positive values that may have been given to them at a young age. Rep who you are like you would your hometown. Put It On everywhere you go like a varsity jacket for everyone.
